        <updateDate>2022-04-06T14:01:34Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p>This bill allows a deduction from gross income (above the line deduction) for attorney fees and court costs awarded with respect to a qualifying wildfire disaster (i.e., any forest or range fire that is a federally declared disaster, occurs in a disaster area, and occurs in 2015 or later). </p> <p>The bill excludes from the gross income of a taxpayer, for income tax purposes, amounts paid to compensate victims for losses or damages in connection with a qualifying wildfire disaster.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
